The paper deals with the problem of reachability in timed automata, which is a topic in formal methods and verification. The use of zones to represent reachable sets is a common technique in this area, which suggests the category cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also proposes a new simulation relation between zones, which is a technique used in program analysis and verification, suggesting the category cs.PL (Programming Languages). The problem of termination in the presence of diagonal constraints involves the manipulation of sets of constraints, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures, suggesting the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses experimental results, which suggests the category cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
